    "We hypothesize that the decline in the relevance scores after -200 ms can be explained by the fact that voice activity information might have already been stored in the long short-term memory of the nVAD model and thus changes in neural activity beyond this time had less influence on the prediction.",
    "Here we demonstrate the feasibility of a closed-loop BCI that is capable of online synthesis of intelligible words using intracranial recordings from the speech cortex of an ALS clinical trial participant.",
    "Recent studies 10, 11, 13, 27 suggest that deep learning techniques are a viable tool to reconstruct acoustic speech from ECoG signals.",
    "We found an approach consisting of three consecutive RNN architectures that identify and transform neural speech correlates into an acoustic waveform that can be streamed over the loudspeaker as neurofeedback, resulting in an 80% intelligibility score on a closed-vocabulary, keyword reading task.",
    "The majority of human listeners were able to correctly recognize most synthesized words."
